page.title: 12HAINAULT FOREST
page.content:
The chief keeper's name is Mr.Morton. In the forest, insects bother the staff alot.Shooting isn't allowed. Some of their rare birds are the Owl, Tiny Warbler, and the Goldcrest. There are keepers to stop poachers killing the animals, which are the Fox, Stoat, Weasel, Rabbit, Vole, Badger, Shrew, and Squirrel. Squirrels and Rabbits are pests, because they burrow into the golf courses and they gnaw at the buds of new trees.
Any tresspassers get arrested. It is very dark and dangerous at night. Lots of people fish in the six ponds, and very recently someone has even drowned. Some people have become lost in the woods.
